commentary: Tsotsobe to Asad Shafiq, OUT The bouncer does the trick. Langeveldt had tried it before but Asad Shafiq managed to connect with the pull shot on that occasion. He has the tendency to get on to the front foot a touch too early and hence the bouncers. This time around, Tsotsobe's bouncer came on to him quickly and he was in no position to play that shot. He was late on the pull and ended up swatting it to mid-on.

text: The bouncer does the trick. Langeveldt had tried it before but Asad Shafiq managed to connect with the pull shot on that occasion. He has the tendency to get on to the front foot a touch too early and hence the bouncers. This time around, Tsotsobe's bouncer came on to him quickly and he was in no position to play that shot. He was late on the pull and ended up swatting it to mid-on.

commentary: Botha to Younis Khan, OUT gone. Botha nails Younis on the sweep. That was tossed up, landed outside off and was turning in as Younis reached across to sweep. He missed and it rapped him on the pads. Was it hitting outside the line of off? Replays suggest it hit Younis just outside the line of off. Asad Rauf doesn't think so. Well played Younis, but this is a huge moment in this game.

commentary: Tsotsobe to Abdul Razzaq, OUT Lovely catch from AB. Tsotsobe, who had a good Twenty20 series, is doing it again in the ODIs. Pakistan crumbling here.

commentary: Langeveldt to Fawad Alam, OUT Does anyone get surprised anymore with these collapses? Comfortably Numb. This one lands on a length on the middle and moves towards the off stump. Fawad Alam didn't do much to prevent it from going towards its destination; he crouched and stabbed at it but the ball escaped his poor attempts, to stop it, collided with the inside edge and fell on the off stump. Clatter.

commentary: Shoaib Akhtar to Smith, no run Amla is almost run out. It was a quick bouncer, Smith was late on the pull and he jabbed it to square-leg. Asad threw the ball at the non-striker's end where Amla had backed up too far ... he ran between the stumps and the throw and managed to get back. The ball rolled past the stumps. Meanwhile, Smith is in pain. That bouncer hit him flush on the gloves. He has already had lots of problems with injuries to his hands. This one struck him on the left hand. The magic spray is out now.

Meanwhile, Smith is in pain. That bouncer hit him flush on the gloves. He has already had lots of problems with injuries to his hands. This one struck him on the left hand. The magic spray is out now.

commentary: Saeed Ajmal to Amla, OUT It was around the off-stump line and Amla pressed back in a hurry as the ball skidded on. The bat came down but the ball skidded on quicker. Have to see the replay to really see where it hit him. So please to wait. Amla wasn't too happy with the verdict. Hawk eye shows that it would have hit the off stump of Amla. It landed on the middle and skidded on towards the off. It also kept a touch low.

commentary: Abdul Razzaq to Kallis, SIX runs Well, that's not the first time Razzaq has offered Kallis a leg stump gift, but that is the first time Kallis has made full use of it. commentary: Umar Gul to Kallis, FOUR runs Kallis essays a crisp little pull shot and while everyone else enjoys the timing, placement and utter ruthlessness of the shot, Kallis goes down, writhing in pain, holding the thigh as he crumpled. His face is contorted in pain as he stretches and tries to reach the toes. He is down for the count here
